terns]\ncreated: 2025-12-10\nupdated: 2025-12-11\n---\n\n# Behavioral Patterns\n\n> What I actually do (not what I say I'll do)\n\n## Priorities (from frequency analysis)\n1. Learning\n2. Building\n3. Documenting\n4. Iterating\n\n## Work Patterns / Decision Patterns / Communication Patterns\n[Structured data]\n\n## See Also\n[[Links to related learnings and resonance]]\n```\n\n### 5. DISTILLATION SYNTHESIS FILES (Backup)\n\nIn `/Users/nat/Code/github.com/Soul-Brews-Studio/opensource-nat-brain-oracle/ψ-backup-opensource-nat-brain-oracle/memory/`:\n\n**themes-synthesis.md** (2025-12-11):\n- Comprehensive 27-theme synthesis from retrospectives + learnings + resonance\n- Includes: title, tags, created date, focus statement\n- Grouped by category (Philosophy, Architecture, Discovery, Workflow, Consciousness)\n- Each theme: title + quote + source + pattern description\n- Frequency analysis section\n- Core insight synthesis at end\n\n**THEMES-QUICK.md**:\n- Quick reference version of themes\n- 24 themes condensed with brief descriptions\n- Most frequent topics highlighted\n\n**principle-comparison.md**:\n- Comparison of constitution principles across projects\n- Structured by universal vs platform-specific\n- Shows evolution of principles\n\n### 6. DIRECTORY STRUCTURE HIERARCHY\n\n```\nψ/memory/\n├── logs/              ← Snapshots (raw, ephemeral)\n├── retrospectives/    ← Sessions (medium refinement)\n├── learnings/         ← Patterns (high refinement, 800+ files)\n├── resonance/         ← Soul (★★★★★, mutual agreement)\n├── traces/            ← Discovery logs\n├── reference/         ← External (not self)\n└── [synthesis files]  ← themes-synthesis.md, principle-comparison.md\n```\n\n**Refinement levels**:\n- Resonance ★★★★★ (Most refined, mutual agreement)\n- Learnings ★★★★☆ (Patterns extracted)\n- Retrospectives ★★★☆☆ (Session summaries)\n- Logs ★★☆☆☆ (Raw snapshots)\n- Reference ☆☆☆☆☆ (External)\n\n### 7. KEY INSIGHT FOR `/distill` SKILL\n\nThe distillation process shou