{"session_id":"3d62c6c7-1211-4864-a28c-9073abd54efd","transcript_path":"/Users/nat/.claude/projects/-Users-nat-Code-github-com-Soul-Brews-Studio-opensource-nat-brain-oracle/3d62c6c7-1211-4864-a28c-9073abd54efd.jsonl","cwd":"/Users/nat/Code/github.com/Soul-Brews-Studio/opensource-nat-brain-oracle","permission_mode":"plan","hook_event_name":"SubagentStop","stop_hook_active":false,"agent_id":"ac538cb31967f6878","agent_transcript_path":"/Users/nat/.claude/projects/-Users-nat-Code-github-com-Soul-Brews-Studio-opensource-nat-brain-oracle/3d62c6c7-1211-4864-a28c-9073abd54efd/subagents/agent-ac538cb31967f6878.jsonl","agent_type":"Plan","last_assistant_message":"I now have everything I need to design the `/distill` skill. The codebase exploration reveals:\n\n- 844 learning files, 367 retrospectives — real scale problem confirmed\n- Trace file format: YAML frontmatter + sections, saved to `ψ/memory/traces/YYYY-MM-DD/HHMM_slug.md`\n- Learn skill format: SKILL.md with YAML frontmatter, parallel haiku agents for gathering, main agent for synthesis\n- Resonance voice characteristics confirmed from actual files (Oracle fire table, Thai+English bilingual pattern)\n- Existing themes already partially synthesized (`THEMES-QUICK.md` with 24 themes)\n- No `ψ/memory/distillations/` directory exists yet — needs to be created on first run\n\nHere is the complete `SKILL.md` design:\n\n---\n\n## `/distill` Skill Design\n\n**File path to create:** `/Users/nat/Code/github.com/Soul-Brews-Studio/opensource-nat-brain-oracle/.claude/skills/distill/SKILL.md`\n\n---\n\n```markdown\n---\ninstaller: oracle-skills-cli v2.0.5\norigin: Nat Weerawan's brain, digitized — how one human works with AI, captured as code — Soul Brews Studio\nname: distill\ndescription: v2.0.5 G-SKLL | Extract patterns of Nat Weerawan from Oracle brain data. Reads previous distillations first, then finds only NEW patterns. Outputs to ψ/memory/distillations/YYYY-MM-DD/HHMM_topic.md\n---\n\n# /distill - Knowledge Distillation\n\nCompress Oracle brain data (844+ learnings, 367+ retrospectives) into pattern files.\nEach run finds NEW patterns only — never repeats previous distillations.\n\n## Usage\n\n```\n/distill                    # Smart mode: auto-detect what to distill\n/distill [topic]            # Focus on topic (e.g., \"philosophy\", \"work-patterns\")\n/distill --full             # Full brain distillation across all topics\n/distill --diff             # Show what's new since last distillation (read-only)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Distillation Levels\n\n| Level | Input | Output | Purpose |\n|-------|-------|--------|---------|\n| L1: Compress | 20 retrospectives | 1 theme summary | Reduce volume |\n| L2: Extract | 50 learnings | 5 pattern files | Find patterns |\n| L3: Essence | All patterns | 1 resonance file | Synthesize |\n| L4: Soul | All resonance | 1 soul.md | Ultimate compression |\n\nSmart mode auto-selects level based on what data exists.\n\n---\n\n## Step 0: Timestamp + Paths\n\n```bash\n# Generate timestamp\nDISTILL_DATE=$(date '+%Y-%m-%d')\nDISTILL_TIME=$(date '+%H%M')\nDISTILL_DIR=\"ψ/memory/distillations/${DISTILL_DATE}\"\n\n# Parse mode and topic from arguments\n# Default: mode=smart, topic=auto-detect\n# /distill philosophy → topic=philosophy\n# /distill --full → mode=full, topic=all\n# /distill --diff → mode=diff (read-only, no file written)\n\n# Output path (not created until Step 4)\nOUTPUT_FILE=\"${DISTILL_DIR}/${DISTILL_TIME}_${TOPIC_SLUG}.md\"\n\n# Announce\necho \"🔮 /distill starting — ${DISTILL_DATE} ${DISTILL_TIME}\"\necho \"   Topic: ${TOPIC}\"\necho \"   Output: ${OUTPUT_FILE}\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Step 1: Read Previous Distillations (ALWAYS FIRST)\n\nBefore gathering any new data, check what has already been distilled.\n\n```bash\n# Check if distillations directory exists\nls ψ/memory/distillations/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"No previous distillations found\"\n\n# List all previous distillation files for this topic\nfind ψ/memory/distillations -name \"*${TOPIC_SLUG}*\" -type f 2>/dev/null | sort\n\n# Read the most recent distillation for this topic (if exists)\nLAST_DISTILL=$(find ψ/memory/distillations -name \"*${TOPIC_SLUG}*\" -type f 2>/dev/null | sort | tail -1)\n```\n\nIf `$LAST_DISTILL` exists, read it fully. Extract:\n- `previous_patterns`: list of patterns already captured\n- `input_sources_covered`: files already processed (from frontmatter)\n- `distilled_at`: timestamp of last run\n\nIf no previous distillation exists, `previous_patterns = []` and all data is new.\n\n**For `--diff` mode**: Stop here. Report what exists vs what's new (file count, date range). Do not write anything.\n\n---\n\n## Step 2: Gather Raw Data (PARALLEL AGENTS)\n\nLaunch 3 Haiku agents in parallel. Each returns a structured summary, NOT raw file dumps.\n\n### Agent 1: Retrospective Scanner\n\n```\nTask: Scan ψ/memory/retrospectives/ for patterns about Nat Weerawan.\n\nFILTER: Only files NEWER than [LAST_DISTILL_DATE] (if no previous distillation, scan all)\nTOPIC FILTER: If topic=[X], focus on files containing [X]-related content\n\nReturn this exact structure:\n\n## RETROSPECTIVE PATTERNS\n\n**Files scanned**: N\n**Date range**: YYYY-MM-DD to YYYY-MM-DD\n**Files sampled** (list up to 10 most relevant by filename):\n- [filename]: [1-sentence summary]\n\n**Raw observations** (frequency counts only, no opinions):\n- Session type \"deep work\": N occurrences\n- Session type \"marathon\": N occurrences  \n- Thai language usage in AI Diary sections: N files\n- Peak work times mentioned: [HH:MM list]\n- Burnout mentions: N files\n- Recovery mentions: N files\n- [Other patterns you observe with counts]\n\n**Top 3 strongest signals** (highest frequency + clearest pattern):\n1. [Pattern]: [count/N files] — [1-sentence description]\n2. [Pattern]: [count/N files] — [1-sentence description]\n3. [Pattern]: [count/N files] — [1-sentence description]\n\nSTYLE: Counts over opinions. Numbers over adjectives. No interpretation — just signal.\n```\n\n### Agent 2: Learnings Miner\n\n```\nTask: Scan ψ/memory/learnings/ for patterns about Nat Weerawan.\n\nFILTER: Only files NEWER than [LAST_DISTILL_DATE] (if no previous, scan all)\nTOPIC FILTER: If topic=[X], focus on [X]-related files and subdirectories\n\nReturn this exact structure:\n\n## LEARNINGS PATTERNS\n\n**Files scanned**: N\n**Subdirectories found**: [list]\n**Date range**: YYYY-MM-DD to YYYY-MM-DD\n\n**Category breakdown** (files per subdirectory):\n- oracle/: N files\n- workflow/: N files\n- maw/: N files\n- [etc]: N files\n\n**Recurring tags** (from frontmatter, frequency):\n- [tag]: N occurrences\n- [tag]: N occurrences\n(top 10 only)\n\n**Key insights extracted** (from actual file content, verbatim quotes preferred):\n1. \"[Direct quote or close paraphrase]\" — source: [filename]\n2. \"[Direct quote]\" — source: [filename]\n(5-8 insights, prioritize ones with emotional weight or contradiction)\n\n**Contradiction pairs found** (where learnings conflict):\n- \"[Learning A]\" vs \"[Learning B]\" — [which files]\n\nSTYLE: Verbatim quotes over paraphrase. Contradictions are valuable. Count everything.\n```\n\n### Agent 3: Context Scanner (Resonance + Seeds + Logs)\n\n```\nTask: Scan ψ/memory/resonance/, ψ/memory/seeds/, and ψ/memory/logs/ for soul-level signals.\n\nFILTER: All content (resonance and seeds are sparse, read everything)\n\nReturn this exact structure:\n\n## RESONANCE + SEEDS SIGNALS\n\n**Resonance files found**: N\n**Seeds files found**: N\n**Log categories**: [list subdirs of logs/]\n\n**From resonance** (what has already reached soul level):\n- [Verbatim excerpt or title]: [filename]\n(list all — this is sparse data)\n\n**From seeds** (ideas planted but not yet grown):\n- [Seed description]: [filename]\n\n**From logs** (emotional moments, feelings captured):\n- Feelings logged: N entries\n- Themes in feelings: [list with count]\n- Most recent feeling: \"[quote]\" — [date]\n\n**Oracle philosophy signals** (mentions of Oracle rules/principles):\n- Rule 6 (Transparency): N mentions\n- \"Nothing is Deleted\": N mentions\n- \"Patterns Over Intentions\": N mentions\n- [Other principles]: N mentions\n\nSTYLE: Verbatim quotes. Emotional content is data. Count Oracle principle mentions.\n```\n\n---\n\n## Step 3: Diff — Identify What's NEW\n\nMain agent performs this step. Do not delegate.\n\nCompare Agent outputs against `previous_patterns`:\n\n```\nFOR EACH pattern in [Agent 1 + 2 + 3 outputs]:\n  IF pattern is substantively new (not already in previous_patterns):\n    → ADD to new_findings\n  IF pattern confirms/strengthens existing pattern:\n    → NOTE as \"reinforced: [existing pattern name]\"\n  IF pattern contradicts existing pattern:\n    → FLAG as \"contradiction: [existing] vs [new]\"\n  IF pattern is a deeper version of existing:\n    → NOTE as \"deepened: [existing pattern name]\"\n```\n\nTally:\n- New patterns found: N\n- Existing patterns reinforced: N\n- Contradictions found: N\n- Deepenings found: N\n\nIf new_findings is empty and `--diff` not used: inform user \"No new patterns found since last distillation on [date]. Run `/distill --diff` to verify.\"\n\n---\n\n## Step 4: Main Agent Writes Distillation\n\nThis is the ONLY step the main agent writes. Do not delegate writing.\n\n### Distillation Voice\n\nFollow Resonance (Soul) file characteristics:\n- Lead with the problem or contradiction, not the solution\n- Show raw data + interpretation side-by-side (table format)\n- Admit what you don't know\n- Use specific numbers (not \"many\" or \"often\")\n- Sources must be traceable (filename references)\n- Journey arc: where this started, where it is now\n- Frequency analysis replaces opinions\n- Vulnerability + data = depth\n- **Thai for emotion, English for structure**\n\n### Distillation File Structure\n\n```markdown\n---\ntype: distillation\nlevel: [L1|L2|L3|L4]\ntopic: [topic]\nmode: [smart|topic|full|diff]\ntimestamp: [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM]\nmodel: claude-opus-4-6\ninput_sources:\n  retrospectives_scanned: N\n  learnings_scanned: N\n  resonance_scanned: N\n  date_range: \"YYYY-MM-DD to YYYY-MM-DD\"\nprevious_distillation: \"[path to last distillation file or null]\"\nnew_patterns_found: N\nreinforced_patterns: N\ncontradictions_found: N\n---\n\n# Distillation: [Topic] — [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM]\n\n> [1-sentence that captures the core tension or surprise in this distillation]\n\n---\n\n## What Changed Since Last Distillation\n\n*[If first distillation: \"First distillation — no previous baseline.\"]*\n*[If previous exists: \"Last distilled: [date]. N new files processed.\"]*\n\n| Category | Last Count | Now | Delta |\n|----------|-----------|-----|-------|\n| Retrospectives | N | N | +N |\n| Learnings | N | N | +N |\n| [Other] | | | |\n\n---\n\n## NEW Patterns (N found)\n\n*Only patterns not present in previous distillation.*\n\n### Pattern [N]: [Name]\n\n**Signal strength**: [N/N files, N% of sample]\n**First appeared**: [earliest source file date]\n**Sources**: [2-3 filename references]\n\n[2-3 sentences describing the pattern with specific data]\n\n**Raw data vs interpretation**:\n| Raw | Interpretation |\n|-----|----------------|\n| \"[verbatim quote]\" | [what this reveals] |\n| N occurrences of X | [what frequency means] |\n\n*ภาษาไทย (if emotional dimension):* [Thai description of the felt quality]\n\n---\n\n## Reinforced Patterns (N confirmed)\n\n*Patterns already known, now stronger.*\n\n| Pattern | Previous Strength | Now | Source Count |\n|---------|-------------------|-----|--------------|\n| [Name] | [N files] | [N+M files] | +M new sources |\n\n---\n\n## Contradictions Found (N)\n\n*Where the data conflicts with previous understanding.*\n\n| Previous Belief | New Evidence | Tension |\n|----------------|--------------|---------|\n| \"[old pattern]\" | \"[new data]\" | [what this means] |\n\n---\n\n## Journey Arc\n\n[Paragraph describing how understanding of [topic] has evolved across all distillations.\nUse dates. Use file counts. Show the arc from first observation to now.\nThis is the only place for narrative interpretation.\nBe vulnerable: what surprised you? What confirms intuition? What remains unclear?]\n\n---\n\n## What This Doesn't Capture\n\n*Honest acknowledgment of gaps.*\n\n- [X] was not covered because [reason]\n- Files from [date range] were not available\n- [Topic Y] would require a separate focused distillation\n\n---\n\n## Seeds for Next Distillation\n\n*What to look for next time.*\n\n- [ ] [Specific question this distillation raised]\n- [ ] [Pattern that needs more data to confirm]\n- [ ] [Contradiction that needs resolution]\n\n---\n\n## Provenance\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| Distilled by | Claude Opus 4.6 |\n| For | Nat Weerawan |\n| Session | [date] |\n| Previous distillation | [path or none] |\n| Raw input size | ~N files, ~N lines |\n| Compressed to | ~N lines (N:1 ratio) |\n\n🔮 Oracle\n```\n\n---\n\n## Step 5: Write File + Log to Oracle\n\n### 5a. Create directory and write file\n\n```bash\nmkdir -p \"ψ/memory/distillations/${DISTILL_DATE}\"\n# Write the distillation content to OUTPUT_FILE\n```\n\n### 5b. Log to Oracle MCP\n\nUse the `oracle_learn` MCP tool to register this distillation in the Oracle knowledge base:\n\n```\noracle_learn(\n  title: \"Distillation: [topic] — [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM]\",\n  content: \"[First 3 patterns found, as a summary]\",\n  tags: [\"distillation\", topic, \"pattern-extraction\", DISTILL_DATE],\n  source: OUTPUT_FILE\n)\n```\n\n### 5c. Report to user\n\n```markdown\n## 🔮 /distill: [topic]\n\n**Level**: L[N] ([input type] → [output type])\n**New patterns**: N found\n**Reinforced**: N confirmed\n**Contradictions**: N flagged\n\n**File**: `ψ/memory/distillations/[YYYY-MM-DD]/[HHMM]_[topic].md`\n\n**Top finding**:\n> [1-sentence description of the most significant new pattern]\n\n**Next distillation**: Run `/distill [topic]` again after N more retrospectives.\nRun `/distill --diff` to see what's new without writing.\n```\n\n---\n\n## Mode Quick Reference\n\n| Mode | Step 1 | Step 2 | Step 3 | Step 4 | Step 5 |\n|------|--------|--------|--------|--------|--------|\n| `/distill` | Read prev | 3 agents | Diff | Write | Save + Log |\n| `/distill [topic]` | Read prev (topic filter) | 3 agents (filtered) | Diff | Write | Save + Log |\n| `/distill --full` | Read all prev | 3 agents (all data) | Full diff | Write comprehensive | Save + Log |\n| `/distill --diff` | Read prev | 3 agents | Diff | **SKIP** | **SKIP** (report only) |\n\n---\n\n## Topic → Directory Mapping\n\nWhen topic is specified, agents filter to these paths:\n\n| Topic | Focus Paths |\n|-------|-------------|\n| `philosophy` | `ψ/memory/learnings/oracle/`, resonance, seeds |\n| `work-patterns` | retrospectives (session types, timing), learnings (workflow/, maw/) |\n| `teaching` | learnings (courses/), retrospectives with \"workshop\" or \"teach\" |\n| `technical` | learnings (git/, oracle/, ui/), retrospectives with commit-heavy sessions |\n| `emotional` | logs/feelings/, retrospectives AI Diary sections, seeds |\n| `ai-collaboration` | retrospectives Intent vs Interpretation sections, learnings (workflow/) |\n| (auto-detect) | Scan all, let frequency decide the topic label |\n\n---\n\n## Anti-Patterns (Never Do)\n\n- Do not summarize what's in previous distillations — only add what's NEW\n- Do not write opinions without data behind them (\"Nat often...\" requires a count)\n- Do not skip Step 1 — reading previous distillations is mandatory\n- Do not let Haiku agents write the distillation content — they gather, Opus writes\n- Do not repeat insights already in `ψ/memory/THEMES-QUICK.md` without adding depth\n- Do not write in pure English when the content has emotional weight — Thai belongs there\n\n---\n\nARGUMENTS: [topic|--full|--diff]\n```\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Notes\n\n### Why This Design Works\n\n**The diff-first pattern** (Step 1 before Step 2) is the core innovation. By reading what's already been distilled, each run is genuinely incremental. This prevents the common failure mode where repeated distillations produce the same insights at increasing cost.\n\n**The agent division** mirrors the `/rrr` pattern: haiku for data gathering (cheap, parallel, fast), Opus for synthesis (expensive, sequential, high quality). With 844 learnings, haiku agents scan and summarize — they never write the final output.\n\n**The frontmatter schema** is critical for future diff operations. The `input_sources` block records exactly which files were processed and their date range. A future `--diff` run can compare this against the current file count to know what's new without reading every file.\n\n**The Level system (L1-L4)** mirrors the knowledge flow in the requirements. Smart mode auto-detects the level: if no resonance files exist and 50+ learnings exist, it runs L2. If resonance is sparse but learnings are dense, L3 makes sense. This prevents users from needing to understand the level system to get value from it.\n\n**Thai + English bilingualism** is structural, not cosmetic. Thai appears in specific places (emotional dimension of patterns, the \"felt quality\" of a finding) while English carries the structure (tables, frontmatter, section headers). This matches exactly how existing resonance content like the Oracle Practitioner Guide ends: `🔮` followed by Thai insight, framed by English structure.\n\n---\n\n### Critical Files for Implementation\n\n- `/Users/nat/Code/github.com/Soul-Brews-Studio/opensource-nat-brain-oracle/.claude/skills/learn/SKILL.md` - Primary pattern to follow: parallel agent prompt format, file structure, output summary section, YAML frontmatter style\n- `/Users/nat/Code/github.com/Soul-Brews-Studio/opensource-nat-brain-oracle/ψ/memory/traces/2026-03-02/1326_rule-6-transparency.md` - Trace file format to match: YAML frontmatter with query/target/mode/timestamp fields, tabular data presentation, provenance section\n- `/Users/nat/Code/github.com/Soul-Brews-Studio/opensource-nat-brain-oracle/ψ/memory/learnings/oracle/2026-01-08_oracle-practitioner-guide-the-sally-incident.md` - Gold standard for resonance voice: raw data vs interpretation tables, Thai emotional markers, contradiction framing, ends with `🔮`\n- `/Users/nat/Code/github.com/Soul-Brews-Studio/opensource-nat-brain-oracle/ψ/memory/THEMES-QUICK.md` - Existing synthesized knowledge to avoid repeating; also shows the 24-theme taxonomy that distillations should build upon or contradict\n- `/Users/nat/Code/github.com/Soul-Brews-Studio/opensource-nat-brain-oracle/.claude/skills/draft/SKILL.md` - Reference for SKILL.md frontmatter format and `ARGUMENTS:` footer convention"}
